'''''Brother Jack''''' is the [[debut album]] by organist [[Jack McDuff]] recorded in 1960 and released on the [[Prestige Records|Prestige]] label.<ref>[http://www.jazzdisco.org/brother-jack-mcduff/catalog/#prestige-prlp-7174 Jack McDuff discography] accessed January 15, 2013</ref> 
==Reception==
{{Album ratings
| rev1 = [[Allmusic]]
| rev1Score = {{rating|3|5}}<ref name="Allmusic"/> 
}}
[[Allmusic]] awarded the album 3 stars stating "Recorded in 1960, the session is a transitional one, both for jazz organ and for one of the instrument's leading players".<ref name="Allmusic">Todd, J. [http://www.allmusic.com/album/brother-jack-mw0000866530 Allmusic Review], January 15, 2013</ref> 

== Track listing ==
''All compositions by Jack McDuff except as indicated''
